cbf.engine

Class TestResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • cbf.engine.TestResult

  • public class TestResult
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines the result object structure with the details like entityType (which can be TESTSUITE, TESTCASE, ITERATION, TESTSTEP etc), entityName, actual value of the entity (like tc name, iter name, step name etc), entityDetails, actual entity object which gives complete details of entity, finalRsType, final result of the executed entity startTime, execution start time finishTime, execution finish time msRsType, most significant result msDetails, most significant result's details

      • add

        public void add(TestResult.ResultType rsType,
                java.util.Map checkDetails,
                int significance)
        Updates TestResult object for msRsType, msDetails etc with the current execution check details
        Parameters:
        rsType - result type of the current check like PASSED, ERROR etc
        checkDetails - check details while execution of component
        significance - significance for summarization if -1: ignore for sake of summarization: failure becomes warning (used in case of ignoreIfUnexpected flags) if 0: normal significance; this becomes significant as per rsType if 1: very significant; overrides earlier summaries (used by a RERUN on failure)

      • add

        public void add(TestResult childResult,
                int significance)
        Accumulate a new child result object, by summarizing msRsType, msDetails, finalRsTyle etc.
        Parameters:
        childResult - child result to be added
        significance - significance for summarization if -1: ignore for sake of summarization: (used in case of ignoreIfUnexpected flags) if 0: normal significance; the default if 1: very significance; overrides earlier summaries (used by a RERUN on failure)
